WEDNESDAY MORNING ON THE EARLY SHOW
<http://www.cbsnews.com/sections/earlyshow/main500202.shtml>=20

Harry Smith, Hannah Storm, Julie Chen and Russ Mitchell anchor THE EARLY
SHOW from New York. Dave Price will bring us the weather.=20

Along with the top news of the day, we will also have the following
stories:=20

ANNA NICOLE'S SISTER: NEW BOOK, PT. 2: In the second part of our
exclusive two-part interview with Donna Hogan, the sister of Anna Nicole
Smith, we'll ask Hogan what is was like for the former Playboy Playmate
and reality show star to live in the spotlight. What does Hogan make of
the paternity battle over Anna Nicole's daughter Dannielynn? We'll ask
her Wednesday morning.=20

MOUNTAIN LION ATTACK UPDATE: In January, seventy-year-old Jim Hamm and
his wife Nell went hiking in the Redwood Forest near Eureka, California.
Suddenly, Jim was attacked by a vicious mountain lion. The ambush left
Jim fighting a long road to recovery. The lion had gripped Jim's head in
its jaws, with a clench so tight that his wife of nearly fifty years
thought nothing could deter the beast. But before she even had time to
think, Nell picked up a stick to beat the lion. Eventually, the lion let
go. Miraculously, Jim lived to tell the tale: about the attack, his
wife's courage, and how he is doing today. He and his wife will join us
Wednesday morning with their harrowing tale.=20

MY GENERATION: BRIDES WITH BELLIES: It used to be that women got married
and then had a baby. But increasingly, that is not the case. Celebrities
have made it fashionable to wed while with child, but they are certainly
not the first women to do so. Today, because more and more women are
marrying when they are older, many are pregnant when they do walk down
the aisle. Some women, on the other hand, are waiting to get married
until after their baby is born. What used to be a stigma is now
something brides are flaunting with maternal pride. So what is behind
the trend? Relationship writer Amy Kean will join us with the latest on
baby-on-board nuptials, and why saying "I do" may be a reaction to the
pitter-patter of little feet.=20

PET ALLERGIES: Dogs, just like people, can suffer from allergies and
some of the symptoms: chewing on paws, scratching, licking or recurrent
ear infections. So how can you protect your pooch from the effects of
seasonal allergies? While your pet's vet may have tips, our resident
veterinarian Debbye Turner will join us with her advice on keeping man's
best friend comfortable during allergy season.=20

ACCESSORIZING WITH SPRING BAGS: With the rise of spring, fashion's
hottest accessory very well may be the handbag. But what are the best
picks for every occasion? Whether you are looking for a carry-all to
tote all of your belongings, or a slim clutch for a night out on the
town, choosing a bag that suits you does not have to be a difficult
affair. Kim France, Editor of Lucky magazine, will join us Wednesday
morning with her top picks for spring.=20

GENE SIMMONS PLAYS XBOX: Known for his over-the-top antics and
outrageous displays, Gene Simmons is as bad as he ever was. The KISS
star and family man has a hit reality show and is showing no signs of
slowing down. Wednesday morning, two of the best Guitar Hero video
gamers will join us, along with Gene Simmons, to play Guitar Hero on
XBOX! Simmons will play the bass while the gamers play the game. You
won't want to miss it!=20

If you would like more information on any of these stories or the
broadcast, please click on the following address and e-mail us:=20
earlyshow@cbs.com <mailto:earlyshow@cbs.com>=20

